    "This adjustment allowed the model to handle the specific nuances of footprint outlines while maintaining computational efficiency through depthwise separable convolutions, which helped in preserving critical morphological details.",
    "However, the model's performance is highly dependent on the quality of the input illustrations; low-quality or poorly preserved footprints led to significant classification errors.",
    "In parallel, Lallensack et al. (2022) present the first use of DCNN to discriminate between theropod and ornithischian dinosaur trace fossils.",
    "However, trackways are often highly varied structures, depending on both animal behaviour and substrate properties, necessitating interpretive outlines that are subjective nature and result in information.",
    "The authors also highlight the challenge of distinguishing features related to foot morphology from those influenced by sediment movement and subsequent erosion."
  ]
